questiontext.text:
Level 1

Use a table of Laplace Transforms to find


$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\sin\!\left(8\, t\right)\} $$.


Laplace Transforms table can be found here.
Help on how to insert mathmetical expressions in your answer can be found here.

generalfeedback.text:
From the Laplace Tables,
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\sin\!\left(b\, t\right)\} =\frac{b}{b^2 + s^2} $$
Substituting b = 8, we get:
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\sin\!\left(8\, t\right)\} =\frac{8}{s^2 + 64} $$

Laplace Transforms table can be found here.
Help on how to insert mathmetical expressions in your answer can be found here.

generalfeedback.text:
From the Laplace Tables,
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\sin\!\left(b\, t\right)\} =\frac{b}{b^2 + s^2} $$
Substituting b = 8, we get:
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\sin\!\left(8\, t\right)\} =\frac{8}{s^2 + 64} $$

questiontext.text:
Level 1

Use a table of Laplace Transforms to find


$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\mathrm{e}^{- 3\, t}\} $$.


Laplace Transforms table can be found here.
Help on how to insert mathmetical expressions in your answer can be found here.

generalfeedback.text:
From the Laplace Tables,
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\mathrm{e}^{- a\, t}\} =\frac{1}{a + s} $$
Substituting a = 3, we get:
$$ \small \mathscr{L}\{\mathrm{e}^{- 3\, t}\} =\frac{1}{s + 3} $$
